docs.abstract: Fed up with A.I. companies consuming online content without consent, fan fiction writers, actors, social media companies and news organizations are among those rebelling.
docs.snippet: Fed up with A.I. companies consuming online content without consent, fan fiction writers, actors, social media companies and news organizations are among those rebelling.
docs.lead_paragraph: For more than 20 years, Kit Loffstadt has written fan fiction exploring alternate universes for “Star Wars” heroes and “Buffy the Vampire Slayer” villains, sharing her stories free online.

headline.main: ‘Not for Machines to Harvest’: Data Revolts Break Out Against A.I.
headline.print_headline: Creators Lead Data Rebellion To Protest A.I.

byline.original: By Sheera Frenkel and Stuart A. Thompson

docs.abstract: The company’s profit topped $20 billion as it pointed to early interest in its artificial intelligence products.
docs.snippet: The company’s profit topped $20 billion as it pointed to early interest in its artificial intelligence products.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft reported record sales and profits on Tuesday, as it shook off recession fears and began seeing the early impacts of its investments in generative artificial intelligence.
